</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="25E951B228C8A8107861575B03D192E2" pageId="7" pageNumber="86" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B6B88673177644430D98EA8DABFE374F" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1CE53FFC26BB713F55EAF17B0593EC46" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">
This species is one of the most widespread 
<taxonomicName id="1647AF93A1913142DB08F72D3E7B312B" lsidName="" pageId="7" pageNumber="86" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Drusinae">Drusinae</taxonomicName>
species, covering all major European mountain ranges from the Carpathians to the Pyrenees (ecoregions 1-10) (Fig. 11).
</paragraph>
